@116  = ~(On Ajantis' face is a stern expression of concentration and vigilance, and his brows are creased with frown lines. You can tell he shaved flawlessly, and his skin is tanned from long hours outdoors.)~
@117  = ~(The outline of Ajantis' armor and clothes provides a suggestion of muscular shoulders and arms. They are not bulky, yet they display the strength gained by years of hard training.)~
@118  = ~(Ajantis' hands are big, yet not clumsy. They are tanned, and his fingernails are cut short and clean. As usual, one of his hands lays on his weapon's hilt, ready to draw it with a firm grip if necessary.)~
@119  = ~(Ajantis stands upright, his expression radiating vigilance, loyalty, and a small amount of nervousness. His armor and clothes are in good condition, proving Ajantis' effort in taking care of them. On his cloak, the Ilvastarr's family coat of arms is shown: a metallic green dragon with orange eyes on a gold background.)~
@120  = ~(Ajantis notices your attention and gives you a quick look.) May I help you in any way, my lady?~
@121  = ~(Ajantis notices your attention and turns to you.) Is something wrong, my lady?~
@122  = ~(Ajantis doesn't seem to notice your attention, leaving you a quiet moment for examination.)~
@123  = ~Yes, my lady?~
@124  = ~What did you mean when you said, 'I am there for you as I will be forever more... If you want me to'?~
@125  = ~I did not speak of this in our discussion, but now, since we travel together once more, I must tell you. The thought of your alleged death in the Windspear Hills sends ice-cold shivers down my back... I could not get over the idea of having killed you!~
@126  = ~I know the Ilvastarrs are a noble family with a lot of commitments, and I assume they want you to find a wife that is suitable for these purposes. But couldn't you imagine having a wife that is actually at your side... traveling or even fighting with you?~
@127  = ~My lady... Do not burden yourself with the babbling of a paladin accompanying you. I am sorry if my words confused you.~
@128  = ~It sounded very much like a love confession to me.~
@129  = ~I am not confused, but I *am* very interested. I think you owe me an explanation.~
@130  = ~Well, everything is fine, then.~
@131  = ~I am not naive enough to think that you might not know what it means. But please, leave me this tiny bit of pride. Do not take me by my vow of truth just now, my lady.~
@132  = ~My lady... The restraints my noble birth put on me concerning my possible wife are not as strict as you might think. Being the fourth son, I have more... freedom in my choice.~
@133  = ~Why do you ask me such a question, I wonder... But you are a sweet mystery to me sometimes, my lady. (cough) Let us move on then.~
@134  = ~Waterdeep is also called the City of Splendors. It's one of the biggest cities in Faerûn, a cosmopolitan power characterized by an open, tolerant spirit. It is an important center of trade, and the townsfolk gained their wealth from it.~
@135  = ~Waterdeep lies to the North of Baldur's Gate on the Sword Coast.  It is surrounded by the Sword Mountains to the North, to the South by the Kryptgarden Forest with the River Dessarin, and by the Ardeep Forest to the East.~
@136  = ~The city is ruled by the Lords of Waterdeep, a council of sixteen members who keep their identities secret. The Lords only appear in public wearing masks and are magically protected. There is only one unmasked Lord: Piergeiron the Paladinson, Warden of Waterdeep and Commander of the Watch. He is called the Open Lord of Waterdeep.~
@137  = ~The Most Noble Order of the Radiant Heart is comprised of warriors of all backgrounds who strive to uphold justice and righteousness across Faerûn.~
@138  = ~The Order is headquartered in Athkatla, but its influence is felt across Faerûn.~
@139  = ~Only the finest defenders of the faith are admitted into the ranks of the Order. It is an honor to be inducted, and I am grateful that I have been found worthy.~
@140  = ~I am quite content. I approve of your choice in companions.~
@141  = ~I believe that not all of our companions share our lofty goals.~
@142  = ~I believe that it is best to withhold judgement. Good or evil may be revealed in time, but now is not that time.~
@143  = ~You know that I will not be completely content until we are rid of the evil in our midst.~
@144  = ~I wonder why you should ask me that when it is clear that our values are very different.~
@145  = ~We need to gather gold to recruit allies, but I hesitate to recommend allying ourselves with the Shadow Thieves.~
@146  = ~We should complete our tasks with all possible haste so that we may recover Imoen and defeat the Cowled Ones.~
@147  = ~We must return to the world we know as quickly as possible.~
@148  = ~We need to do whatever we have to do to return to the surface and carry out our quest.~
@149  = ~We need to recover the Rhynn Lanthorn.~
@150  = ~We need to find a way to defeat Irenicus, recover your soul, and overcome evil.~
@151  = ~Helm is the god of vigilance and the protector of the weak.~
@152  = ~Helm is neither cold, nor unfeeling. He commands his servants to protect the rights of all.~
@153  = ~Helm is the eternal sentry. His vigilance never ceases, and thus order is maintained.~
@154  = ~Helm is always ready to defend his followers against those who would do them wrong, but he is just as ready to protect those who have no other advocate. The innocent always have a staunch defender in Helm.~
@155  = ~With pleasure, although I doubt there is anything you don't know already.~
@156  = ~A knight is always vigilant, but if you meant to ask what a knight does between missions, I would say that he does the same things that any other law-abiding person would do: spend time with family and friends.~
@157  = ~Sometimes, it is necessary to recover to regain strength and power, because an exhausted knight is of no use to anyone.~
@158  = ~Wise knights use the opportunity to train. Learning new skills is always rewarding, but maintaining one's fighting prowess is crucial to survival.~
@159  = ~If obligations allow a respite, a period of reflection and meditation can rejuvenate the soul.~
@160  = ~As 'relaxing' would imply lessening my vigilance, I must say that I do not 'relax'.~
@161  = ~I am relaxed. For me, that involves a great deal of attentiveness.~
@162  = ~It is my obligation to be ready for any threat to the safety of this party or of any innocent bystanders.~
@163  = ~It is my duty to remain vigilant. I may not relinquish it.~
@164  = ~Being a paladin of Helm means striving to overcome tyranny and oppression, protecting the innocent, and destroying evil wherever it may hide.~
@165  = ~Upholding the doctrines of one's god.~
@166  = ~A paladin is devoted to his god. The nature of his duties depends on the attributes of the god. Nevertheless, all are champions of justice and righteousness.~
@167  = ~Being a paladin means that one's life is devoted to serving one's god through humble service and dedication to the ideals set forth by that god. Paladins of Helm are vigilant and defend the weak. Paladins of other gods have different duties, but they are no less servants of goodness or righteousness.~
@168  = ~Completely.~
@169  = ~You have the ability to let your deeds shine in a brilliant light, yet I saw you making decisions that show an evil tendency.~
@170  = ~I am, but there is still room for improvement.~
@171  = ~I believe we could do more to help people.~
@172  = ~Since you bid me speak, I must say that I would be happier if you led us toward more glorious deeds.~
@173  = ~I believe this party might benefit from different leadership.~
@174  = ~Then I will remain silent, if my duty permits.~
@175  = ~Very good. Thank you.~
@176  = ~Then I will now remain silent so that we can dedicate ourselves to our duties.~
@177  = ~My lady, I thank you for your kind words.~
@178  = ~Yes, that's true. The Order found me worthy to be lifted to the title of knight. It was the proudest day of my life.~
@179  = ~I am glad for you.~
@180  = ~Where was the ceremony held?~
@181  = ~I did not want to hear every detail.~
@182  = ~It's good to have a knight around. I hope your fighting strength did thus also increase!~
@183  = ~That it did, and likewise my watchfulness. I will use it to keep you in my sight, rest assured, <CHARNAME>.~
@184  = ~The ceremony took place here in Amn, the headquarters of the Order. It was the proudest day of my life.~
@185  = ~It was a great honor for me to attend your knighthood, my young friend. For an old knight like me, it is an uplifting feeling to have aided capable young knights such as you.~
@186  = ~More young comrades followed, as I see it. My congratulations on passing the knight test, Sir Anomen!~
@187  = ~I thank you, Sir Ajantis. Yes, this day is my proudest one, as well. More than half my life I have worked towards this goal, and now it has come true!~
@188  = ~I was very happy, <CHARNAME>. It is the fulfillment of my determination! Since the test, I served the Order and am trying to bring justice and righteousness to the people as a knight.~
@189  = ~This is wonderful, Ajantis. I am glad for you.~
@190  = ~Let us continue on, Ajantis.~
@191  = ~I thank you.~
@192  = ~As you wish.~
@193  = ~Why do you ask? Men and women are equal in the struggle for good.~
@194  = ~Of course. It was just a question.~
@195  = ~Hmm, well, sometimes, something more develops from such a relationship... is that not true?~
@196  = ~(giggle) Sure. But sometimes it is so much nicer to deal with *sisters* of the Order when washing in the river, is it not?~
@197  = ~I do not know what you mean with this remark. All these stories passed... a long time ago.~
@198  = ~Is it really only in the past when a paladin could have feelings for his leader, Ajantis? What if she would reciprocate his feelings?~
@199  = ~Yes, and this is a good thing.~
@200  = ~Let us... end this conversation. I do not know what you object to.~ 
@201  = ~What do you mean by this? I would never...~
@202  = ~That is easily told. The tensions at the Sword Coast and the threatening war with Amn required many missions by the Order. I returned to the headquarters of the Order, was found worthy of knighthood, and was belted to the title of knight.~
@203  = ~But you know that already. There is no more to report. Let us counter the new threats that await us!~
@204  = ~Does the decision of your parents still concern you?~
@205  = ~Ajantis, we have the answer from your parents now. When can we finally get married?~
@206  = ~Ajantis, do not brood any longer. I can no longer bear your agony. I... relieve you from the obligations of our engagement.~
@207  = ~Now it is certain that your parents will disinherit you. Honestly, Ajantis, I had seen myself as 'Lady Ilvastarr'. If you cannot offer that to me, I would not like to marry you.~
@208  = ~Kiss me, Ajantis.~
@209  = ~Ajantis, I need a hug.~
@210  = ~Ajantis, I want to end our relationship.~
@211  = ~(Unlike his usual vigilance, Ajantis doesn't seem to notice your approach. There is a troubled look on his face.)~
@212  = ~Ajantis, your voice sounds... strange.~
@213  = ~<CHARNAME>... I am sorry, but not now.~
@214  = ~(cough)~
@215  = ~Yes, very much. I do not understand it yet. Forgive me, but I need some more time.~
@216  = ~<CHARNAME>, my parents threaten to disinherit me if I marry the woman that I love. I need time to understand. Please, have patience.~
@217  = ~You would do that for me? Your unsolicited offer seems noble, but... No, this does not *solve* anything, <CHARNAME>! It would be agony for me to lose you. Please, I need only a little more time.~
@218  = ~You would do this for me? Your suggestion seems noble, <CHARNAME>. Do not think that my love for you has diminished, but... Maybe it would be better... If you want it, then we could do so.~
@219  = ~On second thought, I do not want to lose you. Let me show you that I am an appropriate wife for a knight, and you can take your strength from me, if your parents turn away from you.~
@220  = ~So easily you agree? Then maybe it is really for the best! We will end our engagement.~
@221  = ~If... if you say so, then it is indeed for the best if we end our engagement, <CHARNAME>.~
@222  = ~On the other hand, I would not want to lose you, Ajantis. Please forget that I brought this up.~
@223  = ~Yes, beloved? Sorry if I push, but have you chosen a wedding ring?~ [c#ablank]
@224  = ~Yes. I would like the ornate ring, adorned with a star sapphire.~
@225  = ~Yes. I would like the ornate ring, adorned with an emerald.~
@226  = ~Yes. I would like the ornate ring, adorned with an opal.~
@227  = ~Yes. I would like the ornate ring, adorned with a ruby.~
@228  = ~Yes. I would like the ornate ring, adorned with a sunstone.~
@229  = ~Yes. I would like the ornate, stoneless ring.~
@230  = ~Yes. I would like the plain ring, adorned with a star sapphire.~
@231  = ~Yes. I would like the plain ring, adorned with an emerald.~
@232  = ~Yes. I would like the plain ring, adorned by an opal.~
@233  = ~Yes. I would like the plain ring, adorned by a ruby.~
@234  = ~Yes. I would like the plain ring, adorned with a sunstone.~
@235  = ~Yes. I would like the plain, stoneless ring.~
@236  = ~What ring would you choose for me, Ajantis?~
@237  = ~No, I have to look at them again.~
@238  = ~My choice is fast and simple. A colorless star sapphire traditionally adorns the finger of a bride, and such a stone I would choose for your ring. Your beauty shines so bright and marvelously that any splendor would pale in comparison, love. In addition, a very intricate ring would perhaps be unfavorable in a fight.~
@239  = ~The plain ring adorned by a star sapphire is what I would choose for you, beloved.~
@240  = ~What a beautiful choice. Yes, I agree.~
@241  = ~Hm, I think I would decide otherwise. I must consider my choice again.~
@242  = ~I am pleased. Master Surianko, you heard the lady. Please, forge us the chosen ring as fast as possible, together with the associated ring for (ahem) a husband.~
@243  = ~Your wish is my command, Sir Knight. I will immediately go to my alternate forge. In just a few days, the finished rings will be waiting for you in the temple of your choice, oh happy bride and groom.~
@244  = ~Your wish is my command, Sir Knight. I will immediately go to my alternate forge. In just a few days, the finished rings will be waiting for you in the temple of your choice, oh happy bride and groom. I allow myself to take my sample bag back, as you will probably no longer need it.~
@245  = ~Your wish is my command, Sir Knight. I will immediately go to my alternate forge. In just a few days, the finished rings will be waiting for you in the temple of your choice, oh happy bride and groom. I assume that you no longer need the sample bag you recently requested, so I will not send it after all.~
@246  = ~Your wish is my command, Sir Knight. I will immediately go to my alternate forge. In just a few days, the finished rings will be waiting for you in the temple of your choice, oh happy bride and groom. I assume that you no longer need the sample bag you recently requested, so I will not send it after all. Although I could have sworn I already sent it... Well, it will all work out.~
@247  = ~Yes, beloved? Sorry if I push, but have you already selected a wedding ring from the sample bag?~ [c#ablank]
@248  = ~Where, please, should I look for it?~
@249  = ~I see no bag with sample rings, Ajantis.~
@250  = ~Open the gemstone bag in my luggage. It is from the master jewelsmith Surianko and contains samples of rings. Take your time on choosing one.~
@251  = ~You are right, the bag is not in my luggage... That is strange. Well, I am afraid that we will have to visit the goldsmith after all, as it seems.~
@252  = ~I am pleased. I will quickly send the bag back, with a message bearing our decision, to Master Surianko. He assured me that he could forge the rings as soon as he knows our preference. I am afraid it will nevertheless take a few days before they are finished.~
@253  = ~Hm, I think I would decide otherwise. Let me look into it once more.~
@254  = ~What can I do for you... Veldrin?~ [c#ablank]
@255  = ~In order to return to the original question: I did not decide the compilation of the group of knights.~

@256  = ~(You look Ajantis straight in the eye.) Male, come here!~
@257  = ~You look thoughtful. Is everything all right?~
@258  = ~I love you.~
@259  = ~You are still the best protector a woman could have.~
@260  = ~Do you like my drow-look?~
@261  = ~I am longing for your touch, Ajantis.~
@262  = ~Let us go into the lust chambers, male!~
@263  = ~(Take a close look at Ajantis.)~
@264  = ~(Hold Ajantis' hand.)~
@265  = ~(Kiss Ajantis' cheek.)~
@266  = ~(Kiss Ajantis' lips.)~
