@571  = ~No, none, but it doesn't matter.~
@572  = ~Then let us finish this villain as soon as possible, <CHARNAME>. He has already taken far too much from you.~
@573  = ~I believe you. Despair not, because I am with you. Continuing with your search is certainly the right approach, whether your dreams have a meaning or not.~
@574  = ~Well, to continue with your search is certainly the right approach, whether your dreams have a meaning or not.~
@575  = ~<CHARNAME>, beloved! My heart beats loudly with joy. I longed for this day from the moment I made the decision to ask you for your hand. I would like to hold and kiss you!~
@576  = ~(You take Ajantis in you arms.) I love you!~
@577  = ~Yes, it is a beautiful moment. (You give Ajantis a kiss.)~
@578  = ~We have important work at the moment, I think.~
@579  = ~You are probably right. We will still have enough opportunities to enjoy our time together. I am thankful that we nevertheless took the time to celebrate our wedding.~
@580  = ~No, this moment I cannot let pass! (Ajantis takes you into his arms and hugs you close for a moment.)~
@581  = ~I am happy to know you now as my wife. Let us stand against the evil of this world together! I swore an oath of loyalty to you, and I say it again: I will be with you and will protect you. We will walk together on the path of righteousness.~
@582  = ~Oh, my friends. My old eyes are actually wet. I wish you all the best for the path you share.~
@583  = ~I wish you all the best, comrades.~
@584  = ~Minsc is happy for his friends. We are so moved that we do not know what we should say, right, Boo?~
@585  = ~Minsc is happy for his friends. Boo would know what to say now. If only Boo were here!~
@586  = ~What-what a joyful moment!~
@587  = ~You have sworn a serious oath and gained a lot of responsibility. May the balance never leave you.~
@588  = ~Tin suit, dry the tears from your eyes. It could be that you do not see my axe coming.~
@589  = ~Amazing what your devotion to this relationship contrives. (Although I am rather surprised that this monkey is even capable of understanding the meaning of such a relationship.)~
@590  = ~Let us leave here. The halls of the ever watchful one are too overwhelming for me. If we are far enough away, perhaps I will honor you and compose an ode.~
@591  = ~Voluntarily celebrating a wedding is a very good thing. I hope you will find your peace.~
@592  = ~I wish that your enemies leave you in peace.~
@593  = ~What strange ritual of self obligation. One man for a woman, what a meager allocation.~
@594  = ~I never thought that I would be present at the wedding of an Order knight...~
@595  = ~Proud and noble you look, Sir Ajantis. I wish you as well, <CHARNAME>, all the best for your marriage.~
@596  = ~An oath before a god reminds us that there are more important commitments than our own. May you never be denied assistance.~
@597  = ~Oh, this reminds me of Aunt Fidelia's wedding. Their third, to be precise. The two earlier were not quite so moving, nor the five thereafter. But their seventh wedding involved a certain amount of comedy, as the former husband of the married aunt Franni, who a year later, married the niece of Uncle Frenkel, or was it his daughter? That is what I was reminded of.~
@598  = ~Now you are married. <CHARNAME>, I wish you all the best. Sir Ajantis, see that you take good care of her!~
@599  = ~Ajantis, I am happy you are now my husband. I will support and protect you, as I swore.~
@600  = ~What you said was beautiful, Ajantis. Thank you.~
@601  = ~Hmm. Let us continue, we have much to do.~
@602  = ~And I love you, <CHARNAME>, from the bottom of my heart. (Ajantis embraces you and gives you a gentle kiss.)~
@603  = ~(Ajantis answers your kiss with passion.) A very beautiful moment!~
@604  = ~That we have, indeed.~
@605  = ~Your words please me, beloved.~
@606  = ~I had hoped that the use of fine velvet and embroidery would weaken the fact somewhat, beloved. But you are right, it is a primarily practical gift.~
@607  = ~I sent it back, since I did not know how long we would be separated.~ 
@608  = ~I sent it back before we came here, since I did not know how long we would be gone.~
@609  = ~I am happy to hear that. He is a widely known, excellent goldsmith, <CHARNAME>.~
@610  = ~I already selected one of the wedding rings from master Surianko. Shall I tell you my choice?~
@611  = ~I assume we will look at the rings again, if the time has come.~
@612  = ~Very gladly, if you wish it. Which pleased you the best?~
@613  = ~I would like the ornate ring, adorned with a star sapphire.~
@614  = ~I would like the ornate ring, adorned with an emerald.~
@615  = ~I would like the ornate ring, adorned with an opal.~
@616  = ~I would like the ornate ring, adorned with a ruby.~
@617  = ~I would like the ornate ring, adorned with a sunstone.~
@618  = ~I would like the ornate, stoneless ring.~
@619  = ~I would like the plain ring, adorned with a star sapphire.~
@620  = ~I would like the plain ring, adorned with an emerald.~
@621  = ~I would like the plain ring, adorned by an opal.~
@622  = ~I would like the plain ring, adorned by a ruby.~
@623  = ~I would like the plain ring, adorned with a sunstone.~
@624  = ~I would like the plain, stoneless ring.~
@625  = ~No, I would not like to decide now after all. I assume we can look at the rings again, when the time comes.~
@626  = ~A fine choice, beloved.~
@627  = ~That is how we will do it.~
@628  = ~It saddens me to hear that, beloved. He is the only goldsmith I know in Athkatla, and... well, I like his selection rather well.~ 


@629  = ~Yes, let us speak about it now. How very much I look forward to the moment!~

